  i  rise  to  support  the  demands  for  grants under the ministry of agriculture for the year 201718  our hon finance minister in his budget speech has announced a number of schemes which will surely bring about  a  revolutionary  change  to  the  agrarian  economy  of  our  country    budget talks about doubling the income of the farmers in the next five years  this years budget  may  be  termed  as  the  budget  for  the  farmers    the  government  has decided to provide about rs 10 lakh crores for agricultural credit  the fasal bima yojana  launched  by  the  government  will  greatly  help  the  farmers  to  face  the challenges  posed  by  natural  calamities   another  milestone  towards  the development  of  agriculture  in  the  country  is  issuance  of  soil  health  cards  government  has  also  set  up  a  long  term  irrigation  fund  and  a  dedicated  micro irrigation  fund  in  nabard  to  achieve  the  goal  per  drop  more  crop    the government has accorded due importance to dairy farming which is an important source  of  additional  income  for  the  farmers    i  would  like  to  request  the government  to  announce  special  package  for  the  farmers  belonging  to  my  state assam  who  have  been  adversely  affected  by  flood  last  year    many  farmers  lost their land and livelihood due to heavy flood and erosion     